        "text": "27. In a school, for a class monitor selection, there are 6 candidates, and students need to choose up to 3 monitors. A student can vote for 1 or 2 or 3 candidates. In how many ways a student can vote?\n(A) 41\n(B) 42\n(C) 43\n(D) 44",
